HEADWORD: Gelding
<hw>Geld"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>gelding</ets> a gelding, akin to <ets>geldingr</ets> wether,
eunuch, Sw. <ets>g⟦aum⟧lling</ets> gelding, Dan. <ets>gilding</ets>
eunuch. See <er>Geld</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A castrated
animal; -- usually applied to a horse, but formerly used also of the
human male.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

